snippet.textDisplay: Random serious talk on a goofy movie review; The idea of the mermaids helping people with their blood brings up a bit of a moral rabbit hole. Should they be forced to give up their blood just because it has healing qualities? "Line them up and just take a little" sounds horrifyingly dictatorial. Does it sound just as innocent and good to say 'hey, lets harvest blood, skin, bone marrow, and kidneys from everyone whether they want to or not so we can do transplants for people who need them!'. We all have stuff we could be donating to help those in need, but we're granted the body autonomy to decide we'd rather not. It would be massively disturbing if the government made donating blood mandatory, especially for kids as young as eleven. Its also mentioned that these healing mermaids are rare. Its not like they'd be able to heal all the people everywhere even if they all drained themselves dry. I don't think any one is obligated to help some one just because they're physically capable of it. People who do go out of their way to help, especially when it's at some personal cost, should be held in high regard, the way volunteer fire fighters and other such people are.
snippet.textOriginal: Random serious talk on a goofy movie review; The idea of the mermaids helping people with their blood brings up a bit of a moral rabbit hole. Does it sound just as innocent and good to say 'hey, lets harvest blood, skin, bone marrow, and kidneys from everyone whether they want to or not so we can do transplants for people who need them!'. We all have stuff we could be donating to help those in need, but we're granted the body autonomy to decide we'd rather not. It would be massively disturbing if the government made donating blood mandatory, especially for kids as young as eleven. Its also mentioned that these healing  mermaids are rare. Its not like they'd be able to heal all the people everywhere even *if* they all drained themselves dry. I don't think any one is *obligated* to help some one just because they're physically capable of it.
